#General-best-practices

Thorough Testing: Test each step in a non-production environment.
Backups: Back up your cluster configuration and critical data.
Monitoring: Monitor cluster health and application performance throughout the upgrade.
Documentation: Keep detailed records of the upgrade process.
Communication: Inform stakeholders about the upgrade schedule and potential disruptions.
Kubernetes Release Notes: Review the Kubernetes release notes for version 1.31 to identify any breaking changes.
AWS EKS Documentation: Regularly refer to the official AWS EKS documentation for the latest best practices.
